Detectives investigating the disappearance of a 'reliable, professional and conscientious' nurse have released CCTV of her last known sighting.

Rui Li, 44, was seen leaving Poole Hospital in Poole, Dorset, on the evening of May 23 before she was reported missing by her family on Tuesday morning.

Police launched a murder inquiry after her car was found yesterday outside a property in Boscombe, Dorset.

Now police have released CCTV showing Ms
 Li driving out of the car park at Poole Hospital at exactly 6.17pm on 
Friday - the last time she was seen.

